 run hydrodynamical simulations. Depending on the braneworld\nmodel, we find differences compared with GR of up to $\\sim15$ per cent in\ngalaxy properties such as the stellar-to-halo-mass ratio, galaxy stellar mass\nfunction, gas fraction and star formation rate density. The amplitude of the\nfifth force is reduced by the presence of baryons in the very inner part of\nhaloes, but this reduction quickly becomes negligible above $\\sim0.1$ times the\nhalo radius.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 27 Jun 2020 23:41:41 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 13 Jun 2021 15:11:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-15"}
