es that\nslow the development of an epidemic too much in the early stages do not\nsignificantly reduce the overall number of deaths in the long term, but\nincrease the duration of the epidemic. In particular, a~hybrid strategy where\nlockdown is held for some time and is then completely released, is inefficient.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 28 Jun 2020 12:14:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 13 Nov 2020 10:40:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-11-16"}
